==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: itself
<hw>it*self"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧t*s⟦ecr⟧lf")</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <def>The
neuter reflexive pronoun of <er>It</er>; <as>as, the thing is good in
<ex>itself</ex>; it stands by <ex>itself</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Borrowing of foreigners, in <qex>itself</qex>, makes not the
kingdom rich or poor.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>itty-bitty</ent>⟦br⟧
